<body>
    <h1>Various Prayers of the Adeptus Ministorum<br><span style="font-size: 13px;">Penned by Friar Petrus-Chriosius&nbsp;</span></h1>
    <p>The God Emperor of Man, master of mankind, is the source of all of man&apos;s strength and our greatest protection against the abomination that dwell in places unseen. Amongst the untold billions that populate the Imperium, the Adeptus Ministorum preaches His word from the teeming slums of hive worlds to the barren wastes of the frontiers. To venerate the God Emperor of Man, the Adeptus Ministorum and it&apos;s faithful have devoted innumerable prayers from a multitude of human traditions. This text aims catalogue many of the payers of the Ecclesiarchy and it&apos;s various chambers from around the Imperium of Man.</p>
    <ol>
