    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Revered Lady, Saint Celestine, Hieromartyr of the Palatine Crusade was originally a Sister of Battle in the Order of Our Martyred Lady. Little is known about her early life or military career prior to her beatification, but it is known that she had taken up the mantle of the Sister Repentia. She fought on the front lines against schismatic traitors to the Imperium and it&apos;s Church, single-handedly fighting off hundreds of foes with her eviscerator chainsword. &nbsp;This would mark the first time she fell. Her sisters, believing her to have been martyred cleansed her body, only to see that her mortal wounds had healed. This miracle granted her the privilege to lead the next charge, which crushed the remaining schismatics on the planet in a matter of hours. <br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Revered Lady quickly became the face of the crusade, winning hundreds of battles on dozens of worlds, each survived with miracles and the protection of the God-Emperor. When all there was to take was the enemy&apos;s capital, she advised otherwise, directing the fleet to a little known world with no strategic advantage. On this world, she was brought to a shrine once visited by Saint Katherine, and entered an unknown crypt only to leave it adorned in the armor and vestments of Saint Katherine, wreathed in blooming flowers and surrounded by the singing cherubim and doves. She was declared a Living Saint before continuing her crusade, destroying the enemy capital and putting a rest to the rebellion. <br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Since that day, Saint Celestene has fought the faithless over long centuries, falling, and rising again from the ashes. At her side are the Geminae Superia Eleanor and Genevieve, who protect her to the last breath each time she is born again. She endures as the God-Emperor&apos;s will made manifest, an agent of His divine protection and everlasting love for His faithful. All who fight in His name know that the situation is never