    <h1>The Virtue of Chastity</h1>
    <p>by Canoness Commander Eleanor-Beatrix</p>
    <p>While the Adeptus Sororitas take no strict vows of celibacy, it is almost unheard of for the faithful warriors of the God Emperor to have romantic relationships. However, this small number seems to be growing. More incidents of fraternization and inappropriate relations are reported. With a growing number of Sisters seemingly forgetting the virtues of restraint and chastity, I have seen it fit to have this missive delivered to each and every mission within my purview. This letter, which will be mandatory reading before confession the day it is received and all Sisters will be expected to reflect on the words written.</p>
    <p><br></p>
    <h2>Your Body is a Temple</h2>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In ancient times there was a phrase &quot;My body is a Temple&quot;. It was a way to express the idea that one must treat their body with the upmost respect. In the modern day, it can better be understood that our bodies are sanctified. We are destined to be martyrs and die for our God-Emperor. Why do you think we adorn our halls with skulls and the bones of martyrs? The Imperial Creed teaches the beauty of the martyr, harrowed and offered freely to Him. By forsaking your chastity and opening yourself to the horrors of the carnal, you open yourself to the unnecessary risks of pestilence and pregnancy. You risk the body that has already been promised as a sacrifice to Him and your ability to serve. </p>
    <h2>What Love is Greater?</h2>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Think Sisters, what love is greater than that of the God-Emperor? Who could possibly be more worthy of your love than Him? Would you forsake Him for wanton flesh? Would you let your gaze wander from His altars for them? You need but one love in your life, one union. Let your helmet be your wedding veil, and your armor a white dress. He is the one who will never forsake you, the only truly unconditional love is His. To offer yourself to another is to say that His love is not enough, that you need the embrace of one other than our God who has sacrificed all for you, who is your greatest servant.</p>
    <h2>Hedonism, the Way of the Enemy</h2>
    <p> &nbsp; &nbsp; We as enforcers of the Ordo Hereticus know what depths hedonism and perversion can drive man to. What better way to steel yourself to the ways of the ruinous powers that rule these heretics than the restraint and grace of chastity? What better way to resist the excessive than by mastering yourself? To give in to your basest desires is to empower the enemy, to resist them is to celebrate the God-Emperor as your master and keeper.</p>
    <h2>Special Instructions</h2>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;This day, on the feast day of Saint Katherine, you will have confession like any other day. If you, or any of your sisters have participated in these carnal deeds, you are to confess, for it is a sin. Sin is written in the heart, not in the law. While there was never a formal vow celibacy codified, it is surely in the spirit of our order. Since you have made yourself bare for others, you will remove your armor before our Emperor&apos;s altar and take on the mantle of the repentia. Only through death will you find absolution for desecrating the body of a future martyr. If any of you fail to confess to your lascivious deeds, you will be subject to mortification upon the inevitable discovery of your sins. <br><br>Death in service to the God-Emperor is it&apos;s own reward. Life in failure to Him is it&apos;s own condemnation.<br><br><br></p>
